The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 World Briefs

 Clashes erupt in Lebanon 

 Nahr al-Bared (Lebanon), June 1 (Reuters): Battles raged around a Palestinian refugee camp in north Lebanon today, killing 14 people. 

At least 12 people were killed inside the camp including two soldiers, security sources said. They added that 18 soldiers were wounded. 

 Bush aide 

 Washington (Reuters): Dan Bartlett, a member of President George Bushs Texas inner circle, announced on Friday he is resigning as White House counsellor effective from July 4. 

 Bangla heat 

 Dhaka (Reuters): A heatwave has killed 22 people this week in Bangladesh, where temperatures have soared above 40 degrees Celsius, media reports said. 




